              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="beeches_apr"></a>Purley Beeches Working Party. Sat 7th April 10am - 1 pm</h3>
                <p>We now have three sites to maintain, so rather than clearing another site for planting, a  tidy up of the lower area of the Beeches, path clearing, coppicing and spring bulb planting will be the order of the day, culminating in the ever popular bonfire. All the usual hand tools will be required, particularly bow saws and loppers, not forgetting protective clothing.</p>
                <p>Signs will be posted from the Beech Avenue entrance to the new ‘Base Camp’. Usual start time of 10am all done by 1pm.  Don’t forget your favourite 11’s beverage. I’m not going to make any predictions about the weather, but it has just got to improve soon. We look forward to seeing our usual hard core members and hopefully some of our newer ones as well.</p>
                <p>For further information please email or call Stanley Lowy: 020 8657 3684 or stanlowy@outlook.com, Elizabeth Bennett: bennett_e@sky.com, Mac Court   mac@skyy.me.uk<p>
                <p><%= link_to "Friends of Purley Beeches work programme for 2018", "/resource/fopb2018.pdf" %></p>
              </td>
             <td class="events">
              <%= link_to image_tag("small-images/purley_beeches100.jpg", alt: "Purley Beeches logo"), "/resource/fopb2018.pdf" %>
            </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
